-- Cardinal Health Swaps Fall as Company Says Not in Takeover Talks
-- B y   M a r y   C h i l d s
-- 2010-10-26T18:23:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/cardinal-health-swaps-fall-as-drug-distributor-says-not-in-takeover-talks.html
Credit-default swaps on Cardinal
Health Inc. tumbled after the company said it is not in talks
with an acquirer.  The cost to protect debt issued by Cardinal Health, which
earlier today jumped as high as 160 basis points, fell back to
85 basis points, according to broker Phoenix Partners Group.  “While it is our longstanding practice not to respond to
market rumors and speculation, we are making an exception in
this limited situation,” the company said in a statement
distributed by PRNewswire. “Cardinal Health is not
in discussions with any party regarding an acquisition of
Cardinal Health.  Swaps on the Dublin, Ohio-based company had surged 90.9
basis points since Oct. 13 before today amid speculation the
company could be bought by a private-equity firm using borrowed
money to finance the takeover.    To contact the reporter on this story:
